HEADWORD: Sycophantish
<hw>Syc"o*phant`ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a
sycophant; obsequiously flattering.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Syc"o*phant`ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sycophantish</qex> satirists that forever humor the
prevailing folly.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sycophantism</ent>⟦br⟧
